<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1927628"><term>area</term><meaning id="fs-id1171505277192">The area is a measure of the surface covered by a figure.</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1933603"><term>equilateral triangle</term><meaning id="fs-id1816092">A triangle with all three sides of equal length is called an equilateral triangle.</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171506988885"><term>isosceles triangle</term><meaning id="fs-id1674082">A triangle with two sides of equal length is called an isosceles triangle.</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171497994973"><term>perimeter</term><meaning id="fs-id1171505779039">The perimeter is a measure of the distance around a figure.</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171488172541"><term>rectangle</term><meaning id="fs-id1922026">A rectangle is a geometric figure that has four sides and four right angles.</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171505990665"><term>trapezoid</term><meaning id="fs-id2022585">A trapezoid is four-sided figure, a quadrilateral, with two sides that are parallel and two sides that are not.</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
